TIAA-CREF, the manager of retirement
accounts for teachers, named former  General Electric Co. (GE) 
executive Ronald Pressman as chief operating officer.  Pressman, previously the president and chief executive
officer of GE Capital Real Estate, will report to TIAA-CREF CEO
 Roger Ferguson , the New York-based firm said today in a
statement distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
